  <Name>k__BackingField: Habakkuk
  fancyName: 
  nickname: hab
  language: English
  lang: eng
  version: New Living Translation
  ver: NLT
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'This is the message that the prophet Habakkuk received in a vision.  '
      comments: []
    - title: "Habakkuk\u2019s Complaint"
      content: "How long, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, must I call for help?\n\tBut
        you do not listen!\n\t\u201CViolence is everywhere!\u201D I cry,\n\tbut you
        do not come to save.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Must I forever see these evil deeds?\n\tWhy must I watch all this
        misery?\n\tWherever I look,\n\tI see destruction and violence.\n\tI am surrounded
        by people\n\twho love to argue and fight.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The law has become paralyzed,\n\tand there is no justice in the courts.\n\tThe
        wicked far outnumber the righteous,\n\tso that justice has become perverted.  "
      comments: []
    - title: "\u2019s Reply"
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> replied,\n\t\u201CLook around at
        the nations;\n\tlook and be amazed![COMMENT[0]]For I am doing something in
        your own day,\n\tsomething you wouldn\u2019t believe\n\teven if someone told
        you about it.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:5 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek version reads '
          body: 'Look, you mockers; / look and be amazed and die. '
        - ft: Compare Acts 13:41.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "I am raising up the Babylonians,[COMMENT[0]]a cruel and violent people.\n\tThey
        will march across the world\n\tand conquer other lands.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:6 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: Chaldeans.
    - title: 
      content: "They are notorious for their cruelty\n\tand do whatever they like.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Their horses are swifter than cheetahs[COMMENT[0]]and fiercer than
        wolves at dusk.\n\tTheir charioteers charge from far away.\n\tLike eagles,
        they swoop down to devour their prey.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:8 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: leopards.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201COn they come, all bent on violence.\n\tTheir hordes advance
        like a desert wind,\n\tsweeping captives ahead of them like sand.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They scoff at kings and princes\n\tand scorn all their fortresses.\n\tThey
        simply pile ramps of earth\n\tagainst their walls and capture them!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They sweep past like the wind\n\tand are gone.\n\tBut they are deeply
        guilty,\n\tfor their own strength is their god.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: "Habakkuk\u2019s Second Complaint"
      content: "O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> my God, my Holy One, you who are eternal\u2014\n\tsurely
        you do not plan to wipe us out?\n\tO <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, our
        Rock, you have sent these Babylonians to correct us,\n\tto punish us for
        our many sins.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But you are pure and cannot stand the sight of evil.\n\tWill you
        wink at their treachery?\n\tShould you be silent while the wicked\n\tswallow
        up people more righteous than they?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Are we only fish to be caught and killed?\n\tAre we only sea creatures
        that have no leader?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Must we be strung up on their hooks\n\tand caught in their nets while
        they rejoice and celebrate?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then they will worship their nets\n\tand burn incense in front of
        them.\n\t\u201CThese nets are the gods who have made us rich!\u201D\n\tthey
        will claim.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Will you let them get away with this forever?\n\tWill they succeed
        forever in their heartless conquests?"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "I will climb up to my watchtower\n\tand stand at my guardpost.\n\tThere
        I will wait to see what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says\n\tand how he[COMMENT[0]]
        will answer my complaint.  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Syriac version; Hebrew reads '
          body: I.
    - title: "\u2019s Second Reply"
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me,\n\t\u201CWrite my
        answer plainly on tablets,\n\tso that a runner can carry the correct message
        to others.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This vision is for a future time.\n\tIt describes the end, and it
        will be fulfilled.\n\tIf it seems slow in coming, wait patiently,\n\tfor
        it will surely take place.\n\tIt will not be delayed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CLook at the proud!\n\tThey trust in themselves, and their lives
        are crooked.\n\tBut the righteous will live by their faithfulness to God.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:3b-4 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek version reads '
          body: 'I will take no pleasure in anyone who turns away. / But the righteous
            person will live by my faith. '
        - ft: Compare Rom 1:17; Gal 3:11; Heb 10:37-38.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Wealth[COMMENT[0]] is treacherous,\n\tand the arrogant are never
        at rest.\n\tThey open their mouths as wide as the grave,[COMMENT[1]]and like
        death, they are never satisfied.\n\tIn their greed they have gathered up
        many nations\n\tand swallowed many peoples.  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:5a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Dead Sea Scroll 1QpHab; other Hebrew manuscripts read '
          body: Wine.
      - number: '2:5b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: as Sheol.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut soon their captives will taunt them.\n\tThey will mock
        them, saying,\n\t\u2018What sorrow awaits you thieves!\n\tNow you will get
        what you deserve!\n\tYou\u2019ve become rich by extortion,\n\tbut how much
        longer can this go on?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Suddenly, your debtors will take action.\n\tThey will turn on you
        and take all you have,\n\twhile you stand trembling and helpless.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Because you have plundered many nations,\n\tnow all the survivors
        will plunder you.\n\tYou committed murder throughout the countryside\n\tand
        filled the towns with violence.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhat sorrow awaits you who build big houses\n\twith money gained
        dishonestly!\n\tYou believe your wealth will buy security,\n\tputting your
        family\u2019s nest beyond the reach of danger.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But by the murders you committed,\n\tyou have shamed your name and
        forfeited your lives.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The very stones in the walls cry out against you,\n\tand the beams
        in the ceilings echo the complaint.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhat sorrow awaits you who build cities\n\twith money gained
        through murder and corruption!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Has not the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies promised\n\tthat
        the wealth of nations will turn to ashes?\n\tThey work so hard,\n\tbut all
        in vain!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For as the waters fill the sea,\n\tthe earth will be filled with
        an awareness\n\tof the glory of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhat sorrow awaits you who make your neighbors drunk!\n\tYou
        force your cup on them\n\tso you can gloat over their shameful nakedness.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But soon it will be your turn to be disgraced.\n\tCome, drink and
        be exposed![COMMENT[0]]Drink from the cup of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        judgment,\n\tand all your glory will be turned to shame.  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:16 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Dead Sea Scrolls and Greek and Syriac versions read '
          body: and stagger!
    - title: 
      content: "You cut down the forests of Lebanon.\n\tNow you will be cut down.\n\tYou
        destroyed the wild animals,\n\tso now their terror will be yours.\n\tYou
        committed murder throughout the countryside\n\tand filled the towns with
        violence.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhat good is an idol carved by man,\n\tor a cast image that
        deceives you?\n\tHow foolish to trust in your own creation\u2014\n\ta god
        that can\u2019t even talk!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "What sorrow awaits you who say to wooden idols,\n\t\u2018Wake up
        and save us!\u2019\n\tTo speechless stone images you say,\n\t\u2018Rise up
        and teach us!\u2019\n\tCan an idol tell you what to do?\n\tThey may be overlaid
        with gold and silver,\n\tbut they are lifeless inside.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is in his holy Temple.\n\tLet
        all the earth be silent before him.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Habakkuk\u2019s Prayer"
      content: 'This prayer was sung by the prophet Habakkuk[COMMENT[0]]:  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew adds '
          body: 'according to shigionoth, '
        - ft: probably indicating the musical setting for the prayer.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "I have heard all about you, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\tI
        am filled with awe by your amazing works.\n\tIn this time of our deep need,\n\thelp
        us again as you did in years gone by.\n\tAnd in your anger,\n\tremember your
        mercy.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I see God moving across the deserts from Edom,[COMMENT[0]]the Holy
        One coming from Mount Paran.[COMMENT[1]]His brilliant splendor fills the
        heavens,\n\tand the earth is filled with his praise.  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:3a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Teman.
      - number: '3:3b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew adds '
          body: 'selah; '
        - ft: also in 3:9, 13. The meaning of this Hebrew term is uncertain; it is
            probably a musical or literary term.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "His coming is as brilliant as the sunrise.\n\tRays of light flash
        from his hands,\n\twhere his awesome power is hidden.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Pestilence marches before him;\n\tplague follows close behind.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When he stops, the earth shakes.\n\tWhen he looks, the nations tremble.\n\tHe
        shatters the everlasting mountains\n\tand levels the eternal hills.\n\tHe
        is the Eternal One![COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:6 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: The ancient paths belong to him.
    - title: 
      content: "I see the people of Cushan in distress,\n\tand the nation of Midian
        trembling in terror.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Was it in anger, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, that you struck
        the rivers\n\tand parted the sea?\n\tWere you displeased with them?\n\tNo,
        you were sending your chariots of salvation!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You brandished your bow\n\tand your quiver of arrows.\n\tYou split
        open the earth with flowing rivers.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The mountains watched and trembled.\n\tOnward swept the raging waters.\n\tThe
        mighty deep cried out,\n\tlifting its hands in submission.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The sun and moon stood still in the sky\n\tas your brilliant arrows
        flew\n\tand your glittering spear flashed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You marched across the land in anger\n\tand trampled the nations
        in your fury.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You went out to rescue your chosen people,\n\tto save your anointed
        ones.\n\tYou crushed the heads of the wicked\n\tand stripped their bones
        from head to toe.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "With his own weapons,\n\tyou destroyed the chief of those\n\twho
        rushed out like a whirlwind,\n\tthinking Israel would be easy prey.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You trampled the sea with your horses,\n\tand the mighty waters piled
        high.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I trembled inside when I heard this;\n\tmy lips quivered with fear.\n\tMy
        legs gave way beneath me,[COMMENT[0]]and I shook in terror.\n\tI will wait
        quietly for the coming day\n\twhen disaster will strike the people who invade
        us.  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:16 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Decay entered my bones.
    - title: 
      content: "Even though the fig trees have no blossoms,\n\tand there are no grapes
        on the vines;\n\teven though the olive crop fails,\n\tand the fields lie
        empty and barren;\n\teven though the flocks die in the fields,\n\tand the
        cattle barns are empty,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "yet I will rejoice in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t!\n\tI will
        be joyful in the God of my salvation!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is my strength!\n\tHe makes
        me as surefooted as a deer,[COMMENT[0]]able to tread upon the heights.\n\t(For
        the choir director: This prayer is to be accompanied by stringed instruments.)"
      comments:
      - number: '3:19 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: He gives me the speed of a deer.
